\begin_layout Definition
A method is 
\series bold
kernelized 
\series default
if every reference to an element of the input space 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}\in\cx$
\end_inset

 occurs in an inner product with another element of the input space, such
 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle \psi(x_{1}),\psi(x_{2})\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{2}\in\cx$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Pause

\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The 
\series bold
kernel function
\series default
 corresponding to 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
k(x_{1},x_{2})=\left\langle \psi(x_{1}),\psi(x_{2})\right\rangle .
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

